usdOspfMIB.name: usdOspfMIB

revisions.description: Added usdOspfVpnRouteTag, usdOspfDomainId, usdOspfAreaTeCapable and usdOspfMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex objects.
Key revisions include: o Corrected description for usdOspfProcessId. o Added usdOspfNetworkRangeTable. o Added usdOspfOperState.
Initial version of this MIB module.

usdOspfMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 E-mail: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdOspfMIB.description: The OSPF Protocol MIB for the Unisphere Networks Inc. enterprise.

usdOspfProcessId.name: usdOspfProcessId
usdOspfProcessId.description: An identifier having special semantics when set. When this object's value is zero, OSPF is disabled and cannot be configured. Setting this object to a nonzero value enables OSPF operation and permits further OSPF configuration to be performed. Once set to a nonzero value, this object cannot be modified.

usdOspfMaxPathSplits.name: usdOspfMaxPathSplits
usdOspfMaxPathSplits.description: The maximum number of equal-cost routes that will be maintained by the OSPF protocol. A change in this value will be taken into account at the next shortest-path-first recalculation.

usdOspfSpfHoldInterval.name: usdOspfSpfHoldInterval
usdOspfSpfHoldInterval.description: The minimum amount of time that must elapse between shortest-path-first recalculations. Reducing this value can cause an immediate SPF recalulation if the new value is less than the current value of usdOspfSpfHoldTimeRemaining and other SPF-inducing protocol events have occurred.

usdOspfRefBw.name: usdOspfRefBw
usdOspfRefBw.description: The reference bandwith, in bits per second. This object is used when OSPF automatic interface cost calculation is used.

usdOspfAutoVlink.name: usdOspfAutoVlink
usdOspfAutoVlink.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to have virtual links automatically configured.

usdOspfExtDistance.name: usdOspfExtDistance
usdOspfExtDistance.description: Default distance for external type 5 and type 7 routes.

usdOspfDDPktsRcv.name: usdOspfDDPktsRcv
usdOspfDDPktsRcv.description: Number of database description packets received.

usdOspfLsrPktsRcv.name: usdOspfLsrPktsRcv
usdOspfLsrPktsRcv.description: Number of link state request packets received.

usdOspfLsuPktsRcv.name: usdOspfLsuPktsRcv
usdOspfLsuPktsRcv.description: Number of link state update packets received.

usdOspfLsAckPktsRcv.name: usdOspfLsAckPktsRcv
usdOspfLsAckPktsRcv.description: Number of link state ACK packets received.

usdOspfDDPktsSent.name: usdOspfDDPktsSent
usdOspfDDPktsSent.description: Number of database description packets sent.

usdOspfLsrPktsSent.name: usdOspfLsrPktsSent
usdOspfLsrPktsSent.description: Number of link state request packets sent.

usdOspfLsuPktsSent.name: usdOspfLsuPktsSent
usdOspfLsuPktsSent.description: Number of link state update packets sent.

usdOspfLsAckPktsSent.name: usdOspfLsAckPktsSent
usdOspfLsAckPktsSent.description: Number of link state ACK packets sent.

usdOspfCsumErrPkts.name: usdOspfCsumErrPkts
usdOspfCsumErrPkts.description: Number of packets received with a checksum error.

usdOspfAllocFailLsd.name: usdOspfAllocFailLsd
usdOspfAllocFailLsd.description: Number of LSA HDR allocation failures.

usdOspfAllocFailDbRequest.name: usdOspfAllocFailDbRequest
usdOspfAllocFailDbRequest.description: Number of database request allocation failures.

usdOspfAllocFailAck.name: usdOspfAllocFailAck
usdOspfAllocFailAck.description: Number of LS ACK allocation failures.

usdOspfAllocFailDbPkt.name: usdOspfAllocFailDbPkt
usdOspfAllocFailDbPkt.description: Number of DD packet allocation failures.

usdOspfAllocFailCirc.name: usdOspfAllocFailCirc
usdOspfAllocFailCirc.description: Number of OSPF interface allocation failures.

usdOspfAllocFailPkt.name: usdOspfAllocFailPkt
usdOspfAllocFailPkt.description: Number of OSPF general packet allocation failures.

usdOspfOperState.name: usdOspfOperState
usdOspfOperState.description: A flag to note whether this router is operational.

usdOspfMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex.name: usdOspfMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex
usdOspfMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex.description: Configure the stable router interface id to designate it as TE capable.

usdOspfAreaTable.name: usdOspfAreaTable
usdOspfAreaTable.description: The Unisphere OSPF area table describes the OSPF-specific characteristics of areas.

usdOspfAreaEntry.name: usdOspfAreaEntry
usdOspfAreaEntry.description: The OSPF area entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one area.

usdOspfAreaTeCapable.name: usdOspfAreaTeCapable
usdOspfAreaTeCapable.description: Configure the specified area TE capable to flood the TE information.

usdOspfIfTable.name: usdOspfIfTable
usdOspfIfTable.description: The Unisphere OSPF interface table describes the OSPF-specific characteristics of interfaces.

usdOspfIfEntry.name: usdOspfIfEntry
usdOspfIfEntry.description: The OSPF interface entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one interface.

usdOspfIfCost.name: usdOspfIfCost
usdOspfIfCost.description: The cost value for this interface.

usdOspfIfMask.name: usdOspfIfMask
usdOspfIfMask.description: The mask used to derive the network range of this interface.

usdOspfIfPassiveFlag.name: usdOspfIfPassiveFlag
usdOspfIfPassiveFlag.description: Flag to indicate whether routing updates should be suppressed on this interface. To actively perform routing updates, set this object to disabled(0).

usdOspfIfNbrCount.name: usdOspfIfNbrCount
usdOspfIfNbrCount.description: Number of OSPF neighbors from this interface.

usdOspfIfAdjNbrCount.name: usdOspfIfAdjNbrCount
usdOspfIfAdjNbrCount.description: Number of OSPF adjacent neighbors from this interface.

usdOspfIfMd5AuthKey.name: usdOspfIfMd5AuthKey
usdOspfIfMd5AuthKey.description: The MD5 authentication key. When setting this object, the usdOspfIfMd5AuthKeyId must be specified on the same PDU. For simple text authentication type, use ospfIfAuthKey. Setting this object will have the side effect of adding or updating the correspondent entry in usdOspfMd5IntfKeyTable. If key given has less than 16 octets, such value will be appended with zeros to complete 16 octets. The zeros will appended to the right of the given key. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero.

usdOspfIfMd5AuthKeyId.name: usdOspfIfMd5AuthKeyId
usdOspfIfMd5AuthKeyId.description: The MD5 authentication key ID. When setting this object, usdOspfIfMd5AuthKey must be specified on the same PDU.

usdOspfVirtIfTable.name: usdOspfVirtIfTable
usdOspfVirtIfTable.description: The Unisphere OSPF virtual interface table describes the OSPF-specific characteristics of virtual interfaces.

usdOspfVirtIfEntry.name: usdOspfVirtIfEntry
usdOspfVirtIfEntry.description: The OSPF virtual interface entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one virtual interface.

usdOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKey.name: usdOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKey
usdOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKey.description: The MD5 authentication key. When setting this object, the usdOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKeyId must be specified on the same PDU. For simple text authentication type, use ospfVirtIfAuthKey. Setting this object will have the side effect of adding or updating the correspondent entry in usdOspfMd5IntfKeyTable. If key given has less than 16 octets, such value will be appended with zeros to complete 16 octets. The zeros will appended to the right of the given key. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero.

usdOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKeyId.name: usdOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKeyId
usdOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKeyId.description: The MD5 authentication key id. When setting this object, usdOspfVirtIfMd5AuthKey must be specified on the same psu.

usdOspfNbrTable.name: usdOspfNbrTable
usdOspfNbrTable.description: The Unisphere OSPF neighbor table describes the OSPF-specific characteristics of neighbors.

usdOspfNbrEntry.name: usdOspfNbrEntry
usdOspfNbrEntry.description: The OSPF neighbor entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one neighbor.

usdOspfNbrLocalIpAddr.name: usdOspfNbrLocalIpAddr
usdOspfNbrLocalIpAddr.description: The local IP address on this OSPF circuit.

usdOspfNbrDR.name: usdOspfNbrDR
usdOspfNbrDR.description: The neighbor's idea of designated router.

usdOspfNbrBDR.name: usdOspfNbrBDR
usdOspfNbrBDR.description: The neighbor's idea of backup designated router.

usdOspfSummImportTable.name: usdOspfSummImportTable
usdOspfSummImportTable.description: The Unisphere OSPF summary import table describes the OSPF-specific characteristics of network aggregation into the OSPF autonomous system. With this table, the load of advertising many external routes can be reduced by specifying a range which includes some or all of the external routes.

usdOspfSummImportEntry.name: usdOspfSummImportEntry
usdOspfSummImportEntry.description: The OSPF summary import entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one summary report.

usdOspfSummAggNet.name: usdOspfSummAggNet
usdOspfSummAggNet.description: The summary address for a range of addresses.

usdOspfSummAggMask.name: usdOspfSummAggMask
usdOspfSummAggMask.description: The subnet mask used for the summary route.

usdOspfSummAdminStat.name: usdOspfSummAdminStat
usdOspfSummAdminStat.description: The admin status of this summary aggregation.

usdOspfSummRowStatus.name: usdOspfSummRowStatus
usdOspfSummRowStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the entry.

usdOspfMd5IntfTable.name: usdOspfMd5IntfTable
usdOspfMd5IntfTable.description: The Unisphere OSPF interface MD5 key table describes OSPF-specific characteristics of the MD5 authentication key for the OSPF interfaces. This table is not to be used for the simple password authentication.

usdOspfMd5IntfEntry.name: usdOspfMd5IntfEntry
usdOspfMd5IntfEntry.description: The OSPF interface MD5 key entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one MD5 authentication's interface.

usdOspfMd5IntfKeyId.name: usdOspfMd5IntfKeyId
usdOspfMd5IntfKeyId.description: The OSPF interface this key belongs to.

usdOspfMd5IntfKeyActive.name: usdOspfMd5IntfKeyActive
usdOspfMd5IntfKeyActive.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to have this key active.

usdOspfMd5IntfAuthKey.name: usdOspfMd5IntfAuthKey
usdOspfMd5IntfAuthKey.description: The MD5 authentication key. If key given has less than 16 octets, such value will be appended with zeros to complete 16 octets. The zeros will appended to the right of the given key. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero.

usdOspfMd5IntfRowStatus.name: usdOspfMd5IntfRowStatus
usdOspfMd5IntfRowStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the entry.

usdOspfMd5VirtIntfTable.name: usdOspfMd5VirtIntfTable
usdOspfMd5VirtIntfTable.description: The Unisphere OSPF interface MD5 key table describes OSPF-specific characteristics of the MD5 authentication key for the OSPF interfaces. This table is not to be used for the simple password authentication.

usdOspfMd5VirtIntfEntry.name: usdOspfMd5VirtIntfEntry
usdOspfMd5VirtIntfEntry.description: The OSPF Interface MD5 Key entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one MD5 authentication's interface.

usdOspfMd5VirtIntfAreaId.name: usdOspfMd5VirtIntfAreaId
usdOspfMd5VirtIntfAreaId.description: The OSPF area ID this key belongs to.

usdOspfMd5VirtIntfNeighbor.name: usdOspfMd5VirtIntfNeighbor
usdOspfMd5VirtIntfNeighbor.description: The OSPF neightbor this key belongs to.

usdOspfMd5VirtIntfKeyId.name: usdOspfMd5VirtIntfKeyId
usdOspfMd5VirtIntfKeyId.description: The OSPF virtual interface this key belongs to.

usdOspfMd5VirtIntfKeyActive.name: usdOspfMd5VirtIntfKeyActive
usdOspfMd5VirtIntfKeyActive.description: Set this object to true(1) in order to have this key active.

usdOspfMd5VirtIntfAuthKey.name: usdOspfMd5VirtIntfAuthKey
usdOspfMd5VirtIntfAuthKey.description: The MD5 authentication key. If key given has less than 16 octets, such value will be appended with zeros to complete 16 octets. The zeros will appended to the right of the given key. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero.

usdOspfMd5VirtIntfRowStatus.name: usdOspfMd5VirtIntfRowStatus
usdOspfMd5VirtIntfRowStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the entry.

usdOspfNetworkRangeTable.name: usdOspfNetworkRangeTable
usdOspfNetworkRangeTable.description: The Unisphere OSPF network range table describes the OSPF-specific characteristics of network ranges, encompassing one or multiple OSPF interfaces.

usdOspfNetworkRangeEntry.name: usdOspfNetworkRangeEntry
usdOspfNetworkRangeEntry.description: The Unisphere OSPF network range entry describes OSPF-specific characteristics of one OSPF network range.

usdOspfNetRangeMask.name: usdOspfNetRangeMask
usdOspfNetRangeMask.description: The subnet mask used for the network range. Unlike the mask used under the command line interface (CLI), this object is set in the non-inversed format (i.e. not a wild-card mask).

usdOspfNetRangeAreaId.name: usdOspfNetRangeAreaId
usdOspfNetRangeAreaId.description: The OSPF area ID this network range belongs to.

usdOspfNetRangeRowStatus.name: usdOspfNetRangeRowStatus
usdOspfNetRangeRowStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the entry.

usdOspfCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the Unisphere OSPF MIB. This statement became obsolete when usdOspfVpnRouteTag, usdOspfDomainId, usdOspfAreaTeCapable and usdOspfMplsTeRtrIdIfIndex were added to the basic group.

usdOspfCompliance2.name: usdOspfCompliance2
usdOspfCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Unisphere OSPF MIB.

usdOspfNbrGroup.name: usdOspfNbrGroup
